var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"#HMH.jl","page":"Home","text":"Hierarchical Modular Hypervector application layer — hosts R-HMH episodic memory (§8) and the ColBaC-HDC representation layer (§9), both schemas over the shared HMH encoder (Eq 11 / Eq 84), built on the FactorVSA resonator-VSA substrate. Source: Goertzel (2026), \"Resonator-Factored Hierarchical Hypervector Embeddings\".\n\nHMH is the general construction; R-HMH is its resonant-episodic application and ColBaC-HDC is another application of the same base — so this package, holding both, is HMH.jl.","title":"HMH.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Two-kinds-of-\"done\"","page":"Home","text":"R-HMH is a working episodic-memory leg: encode_episode (Eq 69) → role-masked recover_slot / resonant complete_slot (Eq 73) → consolidate (Eq 77). Its episodic margin gate PASSES (STEP5_GATE_RESULT.md): realistic episodes (≈10 slots, ≈5 relations) recover ≥0.95 at D=512, recovery traces the capacity boundary k ≈ D/(2·ln M), and the negative control collapses with load (a real test, not lossless).\nColBaC-HDC is the representation substrate a causal-coding learner would consume: encode_column (Eq 84) + recover_motif, support_code (Eq 85), certificate (Eq 86–87), and HDC audit quantities (cleanup_margin_of, confusability, reuse_score, promote_signal) — tested on synthetic columns. It is not a working ColBaC learner (that is the separate NGC/FabricPC line).","title":"Two kinds of \"done\""},{"category":"section","location":"#Design-bound","page":"Home","text":"Keep an episode's role-bound load within k_slot + k_rel ≲ D/(2·ln M) (at D=1024, M=64 that's ~120 terms — comfortable for typed episodes). Beyond that, raise D or nest sub-episodes.","title":"Design bound"},{"category":"section","location":"#Usage","page":"Home","text":"using FactorVSA, HMH   # HMH builds on, and does not re-export, FactorVSA's algebra","title":"Usage"},{"category":"section","location":"#API-reference","page":"Home","text":"","title":"API reference"},{"category":"section","location":"#Index","page":"Home","text":"","title":"Index"},{"category":"type","location":"#HMH.Column","page":"Home","text":"Column\n\nA ColBaC column's active motifs (§9.3), each triple-tagged: microcolumn type u ∈ {:K,:L,:B}, shell tier s ∈ 0:3 (0 = hard kernel), local role a, and the motif hypervector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.Column"},{"category":"type","location":"#HMH.Episode","page":"Home","text":"Episode\n\nA typed factor graph (paper §8.2, Eq 68):\n\nschema    — schema / event-type code h_σ(E)\nslots     — role => (type, filler)   (role r_s, ontology type τ, filler h_{f_s})\nrelations — (relrole, role_i, role_j) typed relation between two slots' fillers\nanchors   — anchorrole => payload     (links to external evidence)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.Episode"},{"category":"type","location":"#HMH.RoleBook","page":"Home","text":"A registry of named role atoms (deterministic per name once created; seed externally).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.RoleBook"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.certificate-Tuple{Dict{Symbol, FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}, FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, RoleBook}","page":"Home","text":"certificate(channels, H_m, rb) → Z_m\n\nStructured certificate hypervector (Eq 86-87): r_signature⊗H_m ⊕ Σ_ch r_ch⊗z_ch over the certificate channels (:shared, :specific, :saturation, :demotion, …). Each channel is recovered by unbinding r_ch and cleaning against that channel's codebook.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.certificate"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.cleanup_margin_of-Tuple{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, FactorVSA.Codebook{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}","page":"Home","text":"Cleanup margin Δ (Lemma 1): ⟨c⁺,z⟩ − max_{c≠c⁺}⟨c,z⟩, normalized by D. Higher = cleaner.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.cleanup_margin_of"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.complete_slot-Tuple{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, Symbol, Symbol, RoleBook, Vector{FactorVSA.Codebook{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}}","page":"Home","text":"complete_slot(H_E, role, type, rb, factor_codebooks) → (factors, score)\n\nWhen a slot filler is itself a product h_{f_s} ≈ c_{s,1}⊗…⊗c_{s,F} (Eq 72), recover the noisy filler then run the resonator INSIDE the episode (Eq 73) to recover its factors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.complete_slot"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.confusability-Tuple{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, FactorVSA.Codebook{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}","page":"Home","text":"Confusability M_conf (Eq 54): #{c : ⟨c,z⟩ ≥ ⟨c⁺,z⟩ − γ·D}. 1 = unambiguous; higher = more confusable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.confusability"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.consolidate-Tuple{Vector{Episode}, RoleBook}","page":"Home","text":"consolidate(episodes, rb; weights=nothing) → H_template\n\nEpisodic-semantic consolidation (Eq 77): Normalize(Σ_i w_i H_{E_i}). Episodes sharing rb (the same role atoms) are aligned by construction; a weighted bundle of their codes forms a schema/script/template. Slots whose filler RECURS reinforce in the template; idiosyncratic fillers average out (recoverable common slots = schema formation).\n\nIMMUTABLE-CODEBOOK CONTRACT: the template is a NEW immutable HV (a fresh arena handle). Consolidation does NOT mutate or grow any codebook. To make templates into a cleanup dictionary, build a NEW immutable codebook from them (a new CodebookRef).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.consolidate"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.encode_column-Tuple{Column, RoleBook}","page":"Home","text":"encode_column(C, rb) → H_m\n\nColumn hypervector (Eq 84): Normalize( Σ_{u,s,a} r_u ⊗ r_s ⊗ r_a ⊗ c_{m,u,s,a} ). Same unbind-and-cleanup machinery as the R-HMH encoder reads any tagged piece.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.encode_column"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.encode_episode-Tuple{Episode, RoleBook}","page":"Home","text":"encode_episode(E, rb) → H_E\n\nR-HMH episode code (Eq 69): Normalize( r_schema⊗h_σ ⊕ Σ_s m_τ(s)⊗r_s⊗h_{f_s} ⊕ Σ_{(ρ,i,j)} r_ρ⊗r_i⊗r_j⊗(h_{f_i}⊗h_{f_j})             ⊕ Σ_a r_anchor(a)⊗h_a ).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.encode_episode"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.episode_recovery_rate-NTuple{4, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"episode_recovery_rate(D, k_slot, k_rel, M; trials, rng) → mean slot-recovery accuracy\n\nBuild random episodes with k_slot typed slots (each filler an atom from its own size-M codebook) and k_rel random typed relations; encode (Eq 69); recover every slot by role-masked cleanup; return the mean fraction recovered correctly. The gate sweeps D, k_slot, and k_rel (the last INDEPENDENTLY — relations are heavier crosstalk).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.episode_recovery_rate"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.promote_signal-Tuple{Real, Real, Integer}","page":"Home","text":"promote_signal(reuse, margin, m_conf) → Float64\n\nHDC side of the shell-hygiene promote rule (Eq 89): monotone ↑ in reuse and cleanup margin, ↓ in confusability. The LEARNER combines this with its factorization defect Δ_fact to decide promotion/demotion — that combination is out of scope here (NGC line).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.promote_signal"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.recover_motif-Tuple{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, Symbol, Integer, Symbol, RoleBook, FactorVSA.Codebook{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}","page":"Home","text":"Recover a tagged motif from a column code (role-masked unbind + cleanup), like recover_slot.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.recover_motif"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.recover_slot-Tuple{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, Symbol, Symbol, RoleBook, FactorVSA.Codebook{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}","page":"Home","text":"recover_slot(H_E, role, type, rb, codebook) → HV\n\nRole-masked unbind of slot role (type type) from H_E, then hard-cleanup against the slot's codebook (other slots/relations act as bounded crosstalk). BipolarMAP: bind is self-inverse, so bind(m_τ, bind(r_s, H_E)) exposes the filler.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.recover_slot"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.reuse_score-Tuple{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}, Vector{FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}}","page":"Home","text":"Reuse signal: max |cosine| of motif m against others (cross-column shared-abstraction mass).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.reuse_score"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.role!-Tuple{RoleBook, Symbol}","page":"Home","text":"Get (or lazily create) the role atom named name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.role!"},{"category":"method","location":"#HMH.support_code-Tuple{Dict{Int64, FactorVSA.HV{FactorVSA.BipolarMAP}}, Vector{Int64}, RoleBook}","page":"Home","text":"support_code(encoded, support, rb) → H_S\n\nActive-support code (Eq 85): Normalize( Σ_{m∈S} r_m ⊗ H_m ) over the encoded columns in support (encoded[m] is column m's H_m). Used for support retrieval / context memory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"HMH.support_code"}]
}
